{"name":"Shayari ","id":195,"content":"<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\n\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Ghalib:</span></strong><br />\nGhalib Sharab Peene De Masjid Mein Beth Ker,<br />\nYa Wo Jagah Bata Jahan Khuda Nahi.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Iqbal:&nbsp;</strong><br />\nMasjid Khuda Ka Ghar Hai Peene Ki Jagah Nahi,<br />\nKafir K Dil Mein Ja Wahan Khuda Nahi.</p>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>Faraz:</strong><br />\nKafir K Dil Se Ayah hun Ye Dekh Ker Faraz,<br />\nKhuda Mojood Hai Wahan Per Usay Pata Nahi&hellip;&hellip;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Wasi:</strong><br />\nKhuda To Mojood Dunia Mein Her Jaga Hai,<br />\nTu Jannat Mein Ja Wahan Peene Se Mana Nahi&hellip;&hellip;&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Saqi:</strong><br />\nPeeta hun saqi, gam-e-duniya bulany kay leya..<br />\nJannat main knsa gam ha ? Is leya waha maana nahi.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tabasum:</strong><br />\nJannat say nikala gaya tha adam ko meri<br />\nkia oqat hai Tabasum<br />\nMujhe peeny de yahan ye he mera<br />\nmuqam hai<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Ayyaz:</strong><br />\nPeene K Liya Mukadas Jagay Na Duhand Ayyaz,<br />\nAger Tujha Duniya Sa Hi Ba-Khaber Raha Na Hai.<br />\nPeene Ki Per Kia Zarorat Hai Khuda Ki Kasam,<br />\nSajda Ma Juka Raha Din Raat Is K Nasha Zindagi Bhair Nahi Utra Ga&hellip;&hellip;.</p>\n\n<h2>Galib</h2>\n\n<p>Life: Probably last famous poet during Mughal empire. Lost his all five children. Life&#39;s suffering is a recurrent theme in his poems/ghazals.</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 329px;\">आईना क्यूँ न दूँ कि तमाशा कहें जिसे<br />\nऐसा कहाँ से लाऊँ कि तुझ-सा कहें जिसे</p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 329px;\">फूँका है किसने गोश-ए-मुहब्बत<sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-2\"><a href=\"http://kavitakosh.org/kk/%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%88%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE_%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%81_%E0%A4%A8_%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%81_%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BF_%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B6%E0%A4%BE_%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82_%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%87_/_%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%BC%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AC#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup> में ऐ ख़ुदा<br />\nअफ़सून-ए-इन्तज़ार<sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-3\"><a href=\"http://kavitakosh.org/kk/%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%88%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE_%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%81_%E0%A4%A8_%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%81_%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BF_%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B6%E0%A4%BE_%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82_%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%87_/_%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%BC%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AC#cite_note-3\">[3]</a></sup> तमन्ना कहें जिसे</p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 329px;\">सर पर हुजूम-ए-दर्द-ए-ग़रीबी<sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-4\"><a href=\"http://kavitakosh.org/kk/%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%88%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE_%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%81_%E0%A4%A8_%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%81_%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BF_%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B6%E0%A4%BE_%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82_%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%87_/_%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%BC%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AC#cite_note-4\">[4]</a></sup> से डालिये<br />\nवो एक मुश्त-ए-ख़ाक<sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-5\"><a href=\"http://kavitakosh.org/kk/%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%88%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE_%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%81_%E0%A4%A8_%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%81_%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BF_%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B6%E0%A4%BE_%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82_%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%87_/_%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%BC%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AC#cite_note-5\">[5]</a></sup> कि सहरा<sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-6\"><a href=\"http://kavitakosh.org/kk/%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%88%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE_%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%81_%E0%A4%A8_%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%81_%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BF_%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B6%E0%A4%BE_%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82_%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%87_/_%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%BC%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AC#cite_note-6\">[6]</a></sup> कहें जिसे</p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 329px;\">&quot;गा़लिब&quot; बुरा न मान जो वाइज़<sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-12\"><a href=\"http://kavitakosh.org/kk/%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%88%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE_%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%81_%E0%A4%A8_%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%81_%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BF_%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B6%E0%A4%BE_%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82_%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%87_/_%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%BC%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AC#cite_note-12\">[12]</a></sup> बुरा कहे<br />\nऐसा भी कोई है कि सब अच्छा कहें जिसे</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 329px;\">Gosh-e-muhabbat =&gt; ears of lover</p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 329px;\">afsoon =&gt; magic</p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 329px;\">huzoom =&gt; abundancy</p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 329px;\">musht-e-khak =&gt; a fisful of dust</p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 329px;\">sahra =&gt; desert</p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\">Line 1/2 - Why would not I offer a mirror, that it becomes a spectacle. From where do I bring, that they say it just like you. The poet says why would I not offer a mirror to the beloved. I putting it in front of her and she looking into it with those haughty glances would cause an uproar all around. The gallery would run amok at the sight of this. From where would I bring another such elegant face, that they say she looks &#39;like her&#39;. Consider an alternate setting. The beloved is in veil and the only way to see her face is indirectly in a&nbsp; mirror. The lover says why would I not offer her a mirror. That is the only way to appreciate the beauty of the beloved. But once everyone see her in the mirror, there is tumult in the gathering on account of her glances. The audience now wants to see the beloved, except they can&#39;t. Where would I get another such beautiful face that looks like her so that the gathering calms down.</p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\">Line 3/4 - Who has blown into the ear of love, Oh Lord!. The spell of waiting, that they say as longing. The poet says, O Lord - who is that someone who has breathed into the ear of love, such a charm of waiting which they now call as longing. That is some magic that someone has discreetly recited into the ear of love and tricked it, that spell of waiting. For as soon as love appears, longing also appears instantly at the same moment as if by magic!</p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\">Line 5/6 - On the head due to mob of sorrow of poverty, throw. That one handful of dust, which they call a desert. There is not one or two but a whole multitude of sorrows of my miserable existence has made me throw handful of dust on my head, which people on looking would call it a desert. Pritchett refers to gareebi as countrylessness. This sorrowful state of homelessness and wandering around and my act of flinging dust on myself, which to onlookers would look so bleak and wasted that they would say its a desert.</p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\">Line 7/8 - Ghalib, do not mind it if the preacher speaks ill of you. Is there anyone there? that everyone say good about. The second line can have an alternate interpretation. It can also mean, there is someone out there, about whom everyone speaks good of. Again with lot of Ghalib&#39;s work, the second line can be a fact or question. The poet says do not take it too hard on yourself if the preacher says bad about you. In a questioning tone he says, is there anyone in the world about whom every speaks highly of. There would always be people who would go against what others says. In the factual style, the poet says - yes there someone like that about whom everyone speaks highly of.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>Tha Khwab Me Khayal Ko Tujh Se Mua&#39;amla</p>\n\n<p>Jab Aaankh Khul Gayi, Na Ziyan Tha Naa Sood Tha</p>\n\n<p><br />\nLeta Hoon Maktab-E-Gham-E-Dil Mein Sabaq,</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hunooz</p>\n\n<p>Lekin Yahi Ki Raft Gaya Aur Bood Tha</p>\n\n<p><br />\nDhanpa Kafan Ne Daagh-E-Uyoob-E-Barahnagi</p>\n\n<p>Main, Warna Har Libas Mein Nang-E-Wajood Tha</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Ziyan = Loss, Sood = Profit; Mua&#39;mla = Concern/matter. In dreams, used talk love with you and enjoy. After waking up, found that there&#39;s neither that love talk, nor you.</p>\n\n<p>Maktab = elementary school, Hunooz = Yet,</p>\n\n<p>Uyoob/uyuub = vices, Barahnagi = bareness/nakedness.</p>\n\n<p>Sources: <a href=\"https://www.rekhta.org/urdudictionary\" target=\"_blank\">Urdu Didctionary</a>, <a href=\"http://www.urdushayari.in/2016/07/mirza-ghalib-aalam-jahan-ba-gharaz-e.html\" target=\"_blank\">UrduShayari.in</a></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>मंज़ूर थी यह शक़्ल तजल्ली&nbsp;को नूर की<br />\nक़िस्मत खुली तेरे क़द-ओ-रुख़ से ज़हूर&nbsp;की</p>\n\n<p>इक ख़ूं-चकां कफ़न में करोड़ों बनाव हैं<br />\nपड़ती है आँख तेरे शहीदों पे हूर की</p>\n\n<p>वा`इज़&nbsp;न तुम पियो न किसी को पिला सको<br />\nक्या बात है तुम्हारी शराब-ए-तहूर&nbsp;की</p>\n\n<p>लड़ता है मुझ से हश्र में क़ातिल कि क्यूं उठा<br />\nगोया अभी सुनी नहीं आवाज़ सूर&nbsp;की</p>\n\n<p>आमद बहार की है जो बुलबुल है नग़मा-संज<br />\nउड़ती-सी इक ख़बर है, ज़बानी तयूर&nbsp;की</p>\n\n<p>गो वां नहीं पे&nbsp;वां के निकाले हुए तो हैं<br />\nकाबे से उन बुतों को भी निस्बत&nbsp;है दूर की</p>\n\n<p>क्या फ़र्ज़&nbsp;है कि सब को मिले एक-सा जवाब<br />\nआओ न, हम भी सैर करें कोह-ए-तूर&nbsp;की</p>\n\n<p>गरमी सही कलाम में, लेकिन न इस क़दर<br />\nकी जिस से बात उसने शिकायत ज़रूर की</p>\n\n<p>&lsquo;ग़ालिब&rsquo; गर उस सफ़र में मुझे साथ ले चलें<br />\nहज का सवाब&nbsp;नज़्र&nbsp;करूंगा हुज़ूर कीकी</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://kavitakosh.org/kk/%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%82%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BC%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%B0_%E0%A4%A5%E0%A5%80_%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%87_%E0%A4%B6%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B2_%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%80_%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8B_%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%B0_%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%80_/_%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%BC%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AC\" target=\"_blank\">Source</a></p>\n\n<p>Tajalli - divine light</p>\n\n<p>Kad-o-rukh - body&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Zahoor - egress, emergence, something becoming clear</p>\n\n<p>Wa&#39;iz - advisor</p>\n\n<p>Sharab-e-tahur - heavenly drink/wine</p>\n\n<p>Nagma-sanj - singing in sweet voice</p>\n\n<p>Tayur - bird</p>\n\n<p>Nisbat - relationship</p>\n\n<p>Kya farz h - is it necessary</p>\n\n<p>Koh-e-tur - hills of tuur.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div class=\"pMC\" data-pc=\"1\" data-roman=\"off\">\n<div class=\"w\" data-p=\"1\">\n<div class=\"c\">\n<blockquote>\n<p data-l=\"1\" style=\"width: 329px;\"><span data-m=\"\\1wk7\">chāhte </span><span data-m=\"\\0zgl\">hai&ntilde; </span><span data-m=\"\\1wkx\">ḳhūb-rūyo&ntilde; </span><span data-m=\"\\0bhm\">ko </span><span data-m=\"\\18f5\">&#39;asad&#39; </span></p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 329px;\"><span data-m=\"\\27z6\" style=\"margin-right: 7.6px;\">aap </span><span data-m=\"\\1xds\" style=\"margin-right: 7.6px;\">kī </span><span data-m=\"\\1ftf\" style=\"margin-right: 7.6px;\">sūrat </span><span data-m=\"\\12qz\" style=\"margin-right: 7.6px;\">to </span><span data-m=\"\\22tr\" style=\"margin-right: 7.6px;\">dekhā </span><span data-m=\"o8fh6+Lr+AXX9NxXliUPRviQ1gg4oGZXn9u/9r5oj6+SKP7T7kvPgQeieT7Avr7+\">chāhiye </span></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 329px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div class=\"pMC\" data-pc=\"1\" data-roman=\"off\">\n<div class=\"w\" data-p=\"1\">\n<div class=\"c\">\n<p data-l=\"1\" style=\"width: 427px;\"><span data-m=\"\\0y4w\" style=\"margin-right: 4.5px;\">teshe </span><span data-m=\"\\2tju\" style=\"margin-right: 4.5px;\">baġhair </span><span data-m=\"\\2sjw\" style=\"margin-right: 4.5px;\">mar </span><span data-m=\"\\0xyx\" style=\"margin-right: 4.5px;\">na </span><span data-m=\"\\2gk2\" style=\"margin-right: 4.5px;\">sakā </span><span data-m=\"\\2nn2\" style=\"margin-right: 4.5px;\">kohkan </span><span data-m=\"\\18f5\">&#39;asad&#39; </span></p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 427px;\"><span data-m=\"\\1gxn\">sargashta-e-ḳhumār-e-rusūm-o-quyūd </span><span data-m=\"\\1c3e\">thā </span></p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 427px;\">https://mirza-ghalib.com/tishe-bagher-mar-na-saka-kohkan-asad/</p>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 427px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<h2 data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 329px;\">Others</h2>\n\n<p data-l=\"2\" style=\"width: 329px;\">मेरे हुजरे में नहीं और कही पर रख दो<br />\n<br />\nआसमां लाये हो ले आओ ज़मीन पर रख दो<br />\n<br />\nअब कहाँ ढूढने जाओगे हमारे कातिल<br />\n<br />\nआप तो क़त्ल का इलज़ाम हमीं पर रख दो<br />\n<br />\nउसने जिस ताख पे कुछ टूटे दिए रखे हैं<br />\n<br />\nचाँद तारों को भी ले जाके वही पे रख दो<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - राहत इंन्दोरी</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Note: Jazbaat, Alfaaz are plurals.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://jagjitandchitra.blogspot.com/2015/02/dost-ghamkhwaari-mein-meri-saee.html\">http://jagjitandchitra.blogspot.com/2015/02/dost-ghamkhwaari-mein-meri-saee.html</a></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n","authorId":null,"subject":"literature","tags":["basic","intro"],"img":null,"summary":null,"lastUpdated":"2020-06-29T09:03:56.175+0000"}